      "content": "Ibuprofen can help with the headache and any inflammation that may be causing your dizziness, but don't overdo it. Take just one or two, as directed on the package, and make sure to drink plenty of water. A stiff neck could be from poor posture or tension over the long hours in the library chair, but it could also be a sign of something more serious, like a muscle strain or even a cervical spine issue. If the stiffness persists or worsens, you might want to consider some gentle neck exercises or even a warm compress to help relax the muscles. But for now, just take the ibuprofen, hydrate, and see if that helps clear up the fog and dizziness. If you're still feeling off, it might be worth a quick check-up, but for now, let's try to get you feeling better with some rest and self-care.",
